{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandate that local authorities provide community spaces for everyone",
        "additional_details": "Despite recognition in planning policy that community facilities are important, provision is inconsistent and declining.\r\n\r\nThere is no statutory minimum standard for access to community spaces. Hundreds of community facilities, libraries and day centres have closed in the past decade\r\n\r\nAs a result, individuals \u2014 particularly those experiencing addiction, homelessness, mental health challenges or social exclusion \u2014 are increasingly left without safe, supportive environments.",
        "background": "Introduce a new statutory duty requiring local authorities to meet a minimum standard of community space provision. Every resident must have access to a free or low-cost community space within a 15-minute walk (approximately one mile) of their home, or via accessible public transport.",
